In order to turn off cell flashing across the grid when copying/pasting a cell or cell range, add the following CSS style:

.ag-cell.ag-cell-highlight { 
    background-color: transparent !important;
}

See this shown here: 
https://plnkr.co/edit/AzaW4EU4VrxlhKLj

Note this will also turn off cell flashing when you're updating cells via API.

You prevent column groups by being pinned/dragged by adding CSS to prevent mouse interaction with the column groups. See: 
https://plnkr.co/edit/8WRhaxr9C6BPjSpO?open=main.js

We've added the following CSS class to index.html

.ag-header-group-cell { 
    pointer-events: none; 
}

Note that this CSS class prevents column group cells from being dragged anywhere. This also means you can't resize or reorder column groups. Instead, you'll have to drag the group child columns to resize or reorder the column group indirectly.

AG Grid adds the horizontal scrollbars to the pinned sections so the the styles of the scrollbars match. The horizontal scrollbars in the pinned columns areas can be overridden with the following CSS:

.ag-horizontal-left-spacer, 
.ag-horizontal-right-spacer {
    overflow-x: hidden !important;
}

See this here: https://plnkr.co/edit/tatX3v5HY8gJEuuE?open=main.js

Note that this could look Ok on Chrome for Windows 11 but it will look a bit odd on MacOS, since the spacers will look white and the scrollbar is grey.

